text: Kunar Hembram , is an Engineer turned Indian parliamentarian . He is a working politician. He was elected to the Lok Sabha (the lower house of the Parliament of India) from Jhargram, West Bengal in the 2019 Indian general election as a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party. == References == == Other websites == * Official biographical sketch in Parliament of India website Category:Living people Category:Politicians from West Bengal Category:Members of the Lok Sabha Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians
